<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DIAMONDLIFE&#8482; (BOSCH PIN SLIDE) DISC BRAKES For Vehicles Built Before June 3, 2002 - DESCRIPTION -
        ANCHOR PLATE AND SPLASH SHIELD
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>ANCHOR PLATE AND SPLASH SHIELD</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0404004">Figure 4</hotlnk>
            for Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <para>The anchor plate (Item 6) includes lubricated floating leading guide pin and rubber boot (Item 7) and
            trailing guide pin and rubber boot (Item 8) and anchor plate pad abutments (Item 9) are protected by
            stainless steel slippers (Item 10). A tie bar (Item 11) is used on 73 mm pin slide disc brake only. A splash
            shield (Item 12) helps protect the brake assembly from road contamination.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Several changes have been incorporated within the anchor plate assembly and caliper mounting bolts
                    on vehicles manufactured after June 3, 2002. It is important to recognize that these changes are not
                    found on disc brakes on vehicles manufactured before June 3, 2002, unless a complete rebuild of the
                    anchor plate assembly was performed on the vehicle. The components that have changed are the leading
                    and trailing guide pins
                    <hotlnk document="s040402_X0404013.xml" xrefid="f0404067">(Figure 67)</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="f0404067"/>
                    and
                    <hotlnk document="s040402_X0404013.xml" xrefid="f0404068">(Figure 68)</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="f0404068"/>
                    and caliper mounting bolts
                    <hotlnk document="s040402_X0404013.xml" xrefid="f0404071">(Figure 71)</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="f0404071"/>.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
